IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SUPPORT PERSONS WITH DEVELOPMENTAL & OTHER CHALLENGES TO ACHIEVE A HIGH QUALITY OF LIFE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: INSPIRED BY THE FRANCISCAN VALUES OF COMPASSION, DIGNITY AND RESPECT, WE SUPPORT PERSONS WITH DEVELOPMENTAL AND OTHER CHALLENGES TO ACHIEVE THEIR HIGHEST QUALITY OF LIFE, PERSONAL GROWTH AND SPIRITUAL AWARENESS.THE VISION OF ST. COLETTA OF WISCONSIN, INC. IS TO BE THE PREMIER PROVIDER OF SUPPORT SERVICES FOR ADULTS WITH DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITIES AND OTHER CHALLENGES THROUGHOUT THEIR LIFESPAN. THROUGH DYNAMIC PARTNERSHIPS, EXCEPTIONAL CUSTOMER SERVICE, A DEMONSTRATED COMMITMENT TO QUALITY AND SPIRITUALITY, THE ORGANIZATION WILL WORK WITH PERSONS RECEIVING SERVICES TO ACHIEVE THEIR BEST LIFE POSSIBLE.
IRS990.Desc: ST. COLETTA OF WISCONSIN OFFERS A VARIETY OF RESIDENTIAL AND VOCATIONAL/DAY PROGRAMS FOR PEOPLE WITH DEVELOPMENTAL AND OTHER DISABILITIES. OUR RESIDENTIAL PROGRAMS ARE LOCATED IN BEAUTIFUL, COMMUNITY-BASED HOMES THAT ARE STAFFED ACCORDING TO NEED. ST. COLETTA HOMES, LOCATED IN BOTH WISCONSIN AND NORTHERN ILLINOIS, ARE BUILT TO BE ACCESSIBLE TO ENABLE THE PEOPLE THAT LIVE IN THEM TO AGE IN PLACE TO THE FULLEST EXTENT POSSIBLE. DAY AND VOCATIONAL PROGRAMS ARE PROVIDED IN OUR JEFFERSON OPERATION LOCATION ONLY. THESE PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO PROVIDE A RANGE OF SUPPORTS INCLUDING PREVOCATIONAL TRAINING, WORKSHOP AND COMPETITIVE EMPLOYMENT. ADDITIONAL SUPPORTS ARE PROVIDED FOR SENIOR CITIZENS AND THOSE IN NEED OF DAYTIME CARE THROUGH A COMPREHENSIVE ADULT DAY PROGRAM. OTHER SERVICES PROVIDED BY ST. COLETTA INCLUDE TRANSPORTATION, ADULT EDUCATION AND RECREATION. AS AN ORGANIZATION WITH MORE THAN A CENTURY OF SERVICE, ST. COLETTA PROGRAMS OFFER THE STABILITY TO FOSTER LIFE-LONG RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN CLIENTS, STAFF AND FAMILIES. WITH THE BACKGROUND OF OUR CATHOLIC/FRANCISCAN TRADITION, SPIRITUAL DEVELOPMENT PLAYS A STRONG ROLE IN THE LIVES OF THE PEOPLE WE SUPPORT. THE FRANCISCAN VALUES OF RESPECT, DIGNITY, COMPASSION AND FAITH ARE CORE COMMITMENTS FOR THE ORGANIZATION GUIDING ALL PROGRAMS AS WELL AS DAILY BUSINESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS REQUIRED TO ASSESS WHETHER IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT A TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION ASSUMING THE TAXING AUTHORITY HAS FULL KNOWLEDGE OF ALL INFORMATION. IF THE TAX POSITION DOES NOT MEET THE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT RECOGNITION THRESHOLD, THE BENEFIT OF THAT POSITION IS NOT RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION HAS DETERMINED THERE ARE NO AMOUNTS TO RECORD AS ASSETS OR LIABILITIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE PRIOR TO FILING. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECEIVES A COPY OF FORM 990 PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANY DIRECTOR, OFFICER OR KEY EMPLOYEE WHO HAS AN INTEREST IN A CONTRACT OR OTHER TRANSACTION PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OR A COMMITTEE THEREOF FOR AUTHORIZATION, APPROVAL OR RATIFICATION SHALL MAKE A PROMPT AND FULL DISCLOSURE OF HIS OR HER INTEREST TO THE BOARD OR COMMITTEE PRIOR TO ITS ACTING ON SUCH CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION. SUCH DISCLOSURE SHALL INCLUDE ANY RELEVANT AND MATERIAL FACTS KNOWN TO SUCH PERSON ABOUT THE CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION THAT MIGHT REASONABLY BE CONSTRUED TO BE ADVERSE TO THE CORPORATION'S INTEREST. THE BOARD OR COMMITTEE TO WHICH SUCH DISCLOSURE IS MADE SHALL DETERMINE, BY MAJORITY VOTE, WHETHER THE DISCLOSURE SHOWS THAT A CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS OR CAN REASONABLY BE CONSTRUED TO EXIST. IF A CONFLICT IS DEEMED TO EXIST, SUCH PERSON SHALL NOT VOTE ON, NOR USE HIS/HER PERSONAL INFLUENCE ON, NOR PARTICIPATE (OTHER THAN TO PRESENT FACTUAL INFORMATION OR TO RESPOND TO QUESTIONS) IN THE DISCUSSIONS OR DELIBERATIONS WITH RESPECT TO SUCH CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION. SUCH A PERSON SHALL NOT BE COUNTED IN DETERMINING THE EXISTENCE OF A QUORUM AT ANY MEETING WHERE THE CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION IS UNDER DISCUSSION OR BEING VOTED UPON. THE BOARD, PRIOR TO VOTING ON THE CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION, SHALL MAKE AN AFFIRMATIVE FINDING THAT THE CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION, IF APPROVED, WOULD BE FAIR AND EQUITABLE. THE MINUTES OF THE MEETING SHALL REFLECT THE GOOD FAITH DISCLOSURE, THE FACTS DISCLOSED, WHETHER A QUORUM WAS PRESENT WITHOUT THE INTERESTED DIRECTOR'S PARTICIPATION, AND THE ABSTENTION FROM VOTING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION OF OFFICERS IS DETERMINED BY THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THEN APPROVED BY THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS. SALARY SURVEY INFORMATION FROM SEVERAL SOURCES, INCLUDING THE MANAGEMENT RESOURCES ASSOCIATION, STATE OF WISCONSIN, AND OTHER INTERNET SITES IS REVIEWED AND DISCUSSED. ALL ANTICIPATED COMPENSATION IS BUDGETED AND IT MUST BE APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
